subSubSection.paragraph:
Mandible basic amphipodan (in the sense of 
Watling 1993
), but without palp; incisor toothed; left lacinia mobilis with six teeth (Fig. 1E); seta row on left mandible with five main pappose setae plus accessory setae, right mandible with three main pappose setae plus accesory setae; molar large, cylindrical and triturative with setules around its circumference.
